properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 NM
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 5 at 3:33AM EST until February 7 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds around 25 kt with frequent gusts of 35 to 40
kt and seas up to 8 feet possible.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River
FL out 20 NM.

* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds and seas will begin to pickup
throughout the day Thursday ahead of an approaching cold front
with gale conditions possible by late afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
